Team 3 WLAN BASESTATION README:



Usage is displayed via the input words: 
   h
   /h
   -h
   --h
   ?
   /?
   -?
   --?



USAGE: java BaseStation
        --robustlog
        --nolog
        --nostdcopy
        --sensorport    <#>
        --logport       <#>
        --targetport    <#>
        --target        <IP|HOSTNAME>



Usage Params Explained:

robustlog:
   Turns on hightly granular log statements not needed
   for regular execution. (The default log option
   documents all exceptions from normal behavior.)


nolog:
   Turns off the file log of the sensor to "sensor.log"


nostdcopy:
   Turns off standard output prints of statements that
   are logged.


sensorport <#>:
   Specify the sensor server socket port of the base station.
   (Default is 1429.)


logport <#>:
   Enable a remote log server socket on this port.
   (The default has this server socket and handle disabled.)


targetport <#>:
   Set the socket port of target subscriber's listening server
   (Group 4's listening application)


target <IP|HOSTNAME>:
   Set the name/IP of the host running the subscriber application
   (Group 4's listening application)
